OL,3,CSacked minister breaks silence to
OL,4,Ccriticise Vaughan Gething's actions
OL,6,FThe MS for Delyn was speaking in front
OL,7,Fof colleagues in the Senedd chamber on
OL,8,FTuesday (9 July). It was the first
OL,9,Ftime the former minister for social
OL,10,Fpartnership had spoken out since being
OL,11,Fremoved from the role, having only
OL,12,Freleased a written statement at the
OL,13,Ftime.
OL,15,FVisibly emotional, Ms Blythyn spoke
OL,16,Fabout the impact the experience had
OL,17,Fhad on her mental health, saying that
OL,18,F"it should not be surprising that what
OL,19,Fhappened has been hugely detrimental
OL,20,Fon a personal level".
