OL,6,F"People will now rightly ask whether
OL,7,Fthe First Minister publicly sacked
OL,8,FHannah without sufficient evidence
OL,9,Fthat she was guilty of leaking.
OL,11,F"The personal consequences for Hannah
OL,12,Fof that sacking were clearly enormous,
OL,13,Fand the First Minister owes her a full
OL,14,Fand humble apology."
OL,16,FThe Welsh Government said it wouldn't
OL,17,Frespond to what Hannah Blythyn said
OL,18,Fbecause it was a personal statement
OL,19,Fand that any questions she'd raised
OL,20,F"will be dealt with directly".
